            ['type' => 'image', 'heading' => 'Guardian Air technician performing furnace repair in a New Jersey home', 'image_path' => '/img/heating-hero.webp'],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'When to Replace Your Furnace', 'body' => "Deciding whether to repair or replace your furnace can be tough. These signs usually mean replacement is the smarter long-term investment.\n\nAge — If your furnace is more than 15 years old, it's far less efficient than modern units and more prone to failure. Newer high-efficiency systems can noticeably cut your heating bills.\n\nFrequent Repairs — If you're calling for furnace repair every season, the repair costs often add up to more than a reliable new system would cost.\n\nUneven or Weak Heat — Cold spots and rooms that never warm up properly are a sign your furnace can no longer keep up with your home's demand.\n\nRising Energy Bills — An unexplained jump in heating costs usually means your furnace is losing efficiency as it wears out.\n\nNot sure which way to go? We'll give you an honest assessment and a free replacement estimate — never a hard sell."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Heating Systems We Service', 'body' => "Our licensed technicians install, repair, and maintain every major type of home heating system across New Jersey.\n\nGas Furnaces — The most common and cost-effective option, burning natural gas for fast, powerful, whole-home heat.\n\nOil Furnaces — Common in older New Jersey homes, delivering strong, reliable heat output; we service and tune oil systems of every age.\n\nElectric Furnaces — A great fit for homes without a gas line, using electric heating elements for clean, simple heat.\n\nHeat Pumps — Energy-efficient electric systems that both heat and cool, ideal for year-round comfort and lower operating costs.\n\nBoilers — Steady radiant warmth through hot water, feeding radiators or in-floor heating; we repair leaks, pressure problems, and no-heat issues."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'No-Heat Emergency Service 24/7', 'body' => "A heating failure in the middle of a New Jersey winter isn't something that can wait until morning. That's why Guardian Air offers 24/7 no-heat emergency furnace repair across Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties.\n\nWhen you call, you reach a real person who dispatches a licensed technician fast — fully stocked to handle most repairs on the first visit. Whether it's a failed igniter, a tripped safety switch, or a furnace that simply won't turn on, we restore your heat quickly and safely.\n\nAnd because our pricing is flat-rate, you'll never pay extra for nights, weekends, or holidays. Honest emergency service when you need it most."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Serving Monmouth, Middlesex & Ocean County', 'body' => "Guardian Air provides trusted furnace repair and heating service to homeowners throughout central New Jersey. Our technicians are local, which means faster response times and a team that knows the older oil systems and newer high-efficiency furnaces common to the area.\n\nWe proudly serve Toms River, Freehold, Brick, Old Bridge, Red Bank, and Lakewood, along with surrounding communities across all three counties. From the Ocean County shore to the neighborhoods of Middlesex and Monmouth, the same trusted technicians keep your home warm.\n\nDon't see your town listed? We almost certainly still serve it — give us a call to confirm and schedule your furnace repair or tune-up today."],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does furnace repair cost in NJ?', 'body' => 'Most furnace repairs in New Jersey fall between $150 and $750 depending on the failed part — an igniter or flame sensor is on the lower end, while a blower motor or control board is higher. We always provide a flat-rate quote before any work begins, so you know the full cost upfront with no surprises.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'When should I replace my furnace instead of repairing it?', 'body' => 'Replacement usually makes sense when your furnace is over 15 years old, needs frequent or expensive repairs, heats unevenly, or is driving up your energy bills. If a single repair is minor and the system is otherwise healthy, fixing it is the better value. We give you an honest recommendation either way.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Why does my furnace keep shutting off?', 'body' => 'Short-cycling is most often caused by a dirty air filter restricting airflow, a malfunctioning thermostat, a clogged flue, or an overheating safety switch doing its job. A quick diagnostic visit pinpoints the exact cause and prevents further wear on the system.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Should I choose an oil or gas furnace?', 'body' => 'Gas furnaces are typically cheaper to run and lower-maintenance where a natural gas line is available, which is why most New Jersey homeowners choose them. Oil furnaces remain a strong option for homes without gas service and can deliver very high heat output. We help you compare based on your home and local fuel costs.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How long does a furnace installation take?', 'body' => 'A standard furnace replacement is usually completed in a single day — typically four to eight hours. More involved jobs, such as switching fuel types or modifying ductwork, may take longer. We give you a clear timeline with your free estimate.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What areas do you serve for furnace repair?', 'body' => 'We provide furnace repair and heating service across Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties, including Toms River, Freehold, Brick, Old Bridge, Red Bank, Lakewood, and the surrounding towns. Call us to confirm service to your specific address.'],
        ];
    }

