            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Industries We Serve', 'body' => "We tailor our commercial HVAC and plumbing service to the unique demands of each type of facility.\n\nOffices & Professional Buildings — Consistent comfort for tenants and staff, with discreet scheduling that keeps your workday uninterrupted.\n\nRestaurants & Food Service — Make-up air, refrigeration, and rooftop service that meets health-code standards and keeps your kitchen open for business.\n\nRetail & Shopping Centers — Reliable heating and cooling that keeps customers comfortable and your storefront inviting in every season.\n\nMulti-Family & Property Management — Building-wide HVAC maintenance for apartments and condos, with fast response for tenant emergencies.\n\nDon't see your industry? Tell us about your facility and we'll build a service plan that fits."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Commercial Boiler & Heating', 'body' => "Larger facilities depend on commercial boilers and heating systems that simply can't fail in a New Jersey winter. We service, repair, and replace hydronic and steam boilers, rooftop heating units, and make-up air systems.\n\nFrom pressure and leak diagnostics to full boiler replacement, our technicians keep your building warm, safe, and efficient. We also handle commercial plumbing — water heaters, drain lines, fixtures, and backflow testing — sized for the demands of a busy property.\n\nRegular boiler maintenance keeps your heat reliable and your energy costs down through the coldest months."],
            ['type' => 'section', 'heading' => 'Serving Businesses in Monmouth, Middlesex & Ocean County', 'body' => "Guardian Air serves commercial clients throughout central New Jersey, including Toms River, Freehold, Brick, Old Bridge, Red Bank, and Lakewood. Because our technicians are local, we respond fast when your business needs us.\n\nOur team is licensed and insured for commercial work, NATE-certified, and EPA 608 certified for refrigerant handling (NJ HVACR license available on request) — the B2B credentials property managers and facility owners expect. Whether you manage a single storefront or buildings across all three counties, you get code-compliant work, documented service, and a single point of contact for scheduling and billing."],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you offer commercial HVAC maintenance contracts?', 'body' => 'Yes. We build custom preventive maintenance contracts with scheduled visits, priority response, and detailed service records — tailored to your equipment and budget so problems get caught before they become emergencies.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'What commercial HVAC systems do you service?', 'body' => 'We install, repair, and maintain packaged rooftop units (RTUs), split and ductless systems, commercial boilers (hydronic and steam), and chillers, plus commercial plumbing. We service all major brands across offices, restaurants, retail, and multi-family properties.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How quickly can you respond to a commercial HVAC emergency?', 'body' => 'Our team is available 24/7 for commercial HVAC emergencies. Maintenance-contract clients receive priority dispatch, and in most cases we can have a licensed technician on-site the same day across Monmouth, Middlesex, and Ocean counties.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'Do you service restaurants and retail in Monmouth County?', 'body' => 'Yes. We work with restaurants, retail stores, and shopping centers throughout Monmouth County — including Freehold, Red Bank, and Middletown — handling rooftop units, make-up air, and refrigeration with scheduling that keeps your doors open for business.'],
            ['type' => 'faq', 'heading' => 'How much does a commercial HVAC maintenance contract cost?', 'body' => 'Pricing depends on the number and type of units, visit frequency, and facility size, so we quote each plan individually. Most clients find a preventive contract pays for itself by avoiding emergency repairs and downtime. We provide a clear, written proposal upfront.'],
